## JavaScript

What is JavaScript?
While HTML deals with the structure/content, CSS with the look/presentation, JS is used to manage the behaviour/interactivity of the website and all its elements. 

JavaScript is a scripting language used to make webpages interactive.

HTML → structure

CSS → design

JavaScript → behaviour

It allows developers to change webpage content dynamically, respond to user actions, and control elements displayed on the screen.

Key Parts of Front-End Architecture

1. Structure Layer (HTML)

Defines layout and content of the webpage
Includes headings, sections, forms, navigation, etc.

2. Presentation Layer (CSS)

Controls design, colors, spacing, layout, and responsiveness
Includes animations, positioning, flexbox/grid, etc.

3. Behaviour Layer (JavaScript)

Adds interactivity and dynamic updates
Handles events, form validation, API calls, DOM manipulation

Pros and cons of JavaScript
Pros                                                    Cons
Client-side processing                          Security concerns
Cross-platform                                  Browser compatibility
Easy to learn

What can we do with JavaScript?
JavaScript controls the behaviour of the browser window/DOM (Document Object Model) which
basically means it allows you to manipulate what the user sees on their device. 

